{"author":{"id":"ff90e8c1032712f76e3c119e253ae3a84614b47da224d1a3450b4f469b0523a9"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1548844612,"nonce":"g2/trDUvVpK86DDiZQ4DsvJvUUc=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1ODg5NTY2NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/svpcom/wfb-ng/issues/30#issuecomment-458895665"},"message":"I use PX4 (not ardupilot). It supports up to 2Mb/s for telemetry UART on pixhawk hardware. Mavproxy is slow for arm hardware - use mavlink_router instead. \n```\n[autopilot] \u003c--(uart)--\u003e[mavlink_router]--\u003e(udp 14550)--\u003e[wfb_drone]--...-(wifi)-...[wfb_gs]---\u003e(udp 14550)--\u003e[QGrondControl]\n```\nYour config file for malink-routerd should contains two endpoints:\n1. for /dev/ttyXXX uart (with proper uart speed)\n2. for udp 127.0.0.1:14550 (assuming that wfb_drone **listen** this port)\n\nAlso check that there are no firewall enabled and you add you added to /etc/NetworkManager/NetworkManager.conf:\n```\n[keyfile]\nunmanaged-devices=interface-name:wlanXX,interface-name:wlanYY\n```\nfor all wifi cards used by wifibroadcast","files":null}]}